<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9769484927192></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9769484927192><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3750&mid=9769484927192>reason for not giving npc's no drop items</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3750&mid=9769484927192#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 16th 6:35 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The reason for the removal of giving npc's no drop items is for this:<br><br>Before if someone wanted a nodrop item, all you would have to do is have a higher level (due to the level restrictions of the charm spell line)enchanter loot the nodrop items.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then just have the person who wanted the item duel the enchanter.  The enchanter then charms the person desiring the nodrop item.  That person now has become an npc.  Now the enchanter hands his 'pet' the nodrop item and wham... you have gotten your nodrop item.<br><br>kind of cheap, but it worked.. so they took the ability of giving nodrop items to npc's away.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
